flowRoot.flowPara: Filter out small streaks to get the final WARM day ranges for the year.
For each day, if 60% or more of the selected hours are WARM, then consider the day as WARM.
Query the DarkSky API (many times) to get the last 3 years of hourly weather data for that location. The values we care about are: temperature, humidity and precipitation.
Clip the hours to just include the hours we're interested in (8am - 8pm).
For each hour determine if it is WARM.
Start with the name of a city.
Query the Google Places API to get the city's latitude and longitude.
Combine the 3 years by taking the median WARM hours for each day.
Smooth out the WARM hours / day by applying a median filter (with a 7 day window).
